{
  "text": "Technical success rates of TIPS in children ranges from 78% to 100% and is comparable to the adult literature [CITATION_1] . Pathologies that could benefit from tips are reported in Table 1 . In childhood cancer survivors, signs of hepatic injury are encountered at a median followup of 12 years. The reported prevalence of hepatic late adverse effects varied between 8 and 52.8%. This wide range is due to variable distribution of risk factors for liver damage and to different regimens of the treatment [CITATION_2] .",
